{"title_page": "Superzoom", "text_new": "{{About|lenses for [[Single-lens reflex camera|single-lens reflex (SLR)]] cameras|[[live-preview digital camera|non-SLR digital cameras]] with large focal length zoom lenses|Bridge camera}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2013}}\n[[File:Canon EOS 400D shot with Panasonic FZ5.jpg|thumb|250px|Sigma Superzoom 18-200mm/3.5-6.3 DC Lens attached to the [[Canon EOS 400D]]]]\n\nA '''superzoom''' or '''hyperzoom''' lens is a type of photographic [[zoom lens]] with unconventionally large focal length factors, typically ranging from [[Wide-angle lens|wide angle]] to extreme [[Long-focus lens|long lens]] focal lengths in one lens.<ref name=\"grimm\">{{cite book |first1=Tom |last1=Grimm |first2=Michele |last2=Grimm |title=The Basic Book of Digital Photography: How to Shoot, Enhance, and Share Your Digital Pictures |publisher=[[Penguin Books]] |year=2009 |chapter=4}}</ref><ref>J. Dennis Thomas, Nikon D3300 Digital Field Guide, John Wiley & Sons - 2014, page 124</ref> There is no clear definition of a superzoom lens, but the name generally covers lenses that have a range well above the 3\u00d7 or 4\u00d7 of a standard zoom lens, with lenses being 10\u00d7, 12\u00d7, 18\u00d7, or above considered superzoom.<ref name=\"grimm\"/>\n\nDue to trade-offs in the optical design, superzoom lenses are noted for having poorer optical quality at the extreme focal length ranges, mostly distortion at max wide angle and long lens ranges.<ref>Jon Sparks, Chiz Dakin, Outdoor Photography, Cicerone Press Limited - 2013, Hardware for the Outdoor Photographer</ref><ref>DK, Digital Photography Complete Course, Penguin - 2015, page 124</ref> The long focal lengths normally have to be combined with [[image stabilization]].<ref>Chris Gatcum, The Beginner's Photography Guide, Dorling Kindersly Limited/Penguin - 2013, page 107</ref>As of late 2019 the widest range superzoom lens is the Tamron [[Tamron 18-400mm F/3.5-6.3 Di II VC HLD|18-400mm F/3.5-6.3 Di II VC HLD]] with 22.2x zoom range.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of superzoom compact cameras]] for cameras from 25x zoom and up\n* [[List of bridge cameras]] for cameras from 40x zoom and up\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:Cameras by type]]\n[[Category:Photographic lenses]]\n[[Category:Superzoom| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|lenses for [[Single-lens reflex camera|single-lens reflex (SLR)]] cameras|[[live-preview digital camera|non-SLR digital cameras]] with large focal length zoom lenses|Bridge camera}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2013}}\n[[File:Canon EOS 400D shot with Panasonic FZ5.jpg|thumb|250px|Sigma Superzoom 18-200mm/3.5-6.3 DC Lens attached to the [[Canon EOS 400D]]]]\n\nA '''superzoom''' or '''hyperzoom''' lens is a type of photographic [[zoom lens]] with unconventionally large focal length factors, typically ranging from [[Wide-angle lens|wide angle]] to extreme [[Long-focus lens|long lens]] focal lengths in one lens.<ref name=\"grimm\">{{cite book |first1=Tom |last1=Grimm |first2=Michele |last2=Grimm |title=The Basic Book of Digital Photography: How to Shoot, Enhance, and Share Your Digital Pictures |publisher=[[Penguin Books]] |year=2009 |chapter=4}}</ref><ref>J. Dennis Thomas, Nikon D3300 Digital Field Guide, John Wiley & Sons - 2014, page 124</ref> There is no clear definition of a superzoom lens, but the name generally covers lenses that have a range well above the 3\u00d7 or 4\u00d7 of a standard zoom lens, with lenses being 10\u00d7, 12\u00d7, 18\u00d7, or above considered superzoom.<ref name=\"grimm\"/>\n\nDue to trade-offs in the optical design, superzoom lenses are noted for having poorer optical quality at the extreme focal length ranges, mostly distortion at max wide angle and long lens ranges.<ref>Jon Sparks, Chiz Dakin, Outdoor Photography, Cicerone Press Limited - 2013, Hardware for the Outdoor Photographer</ref><ref>DK, Digital Photography Complete Course, Penguin - 2015, page 124</ref> The long focal lengths normally have to be combined with [[image stabilization]].<ref>Chris Gatcum, The Beginner's Photography Guide, Dorling Kindersly Limited/Penguin - 2013, page 107</ref>As of late 2019 the widest range superzoom lens is the Tamron [[Tamron 18-400mm F/3.5-6.3 Di II VC HLD|18-400mm F/3.5-6.3 Di II VC HLD]] with 22.2x zoom range.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of superzoom compact cameras]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:Cameras by type]]\n[[Category:Photographic lenses]]\n[[Category:Superzoom| ]]\n", "name_user": "85.23.156.109", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eSee also)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superzoom"}
{"title_page": "Grace Wong", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{infobox person\n| name = Grace Wong\n| image = Grace Wong.jpg\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1986|5|5}}\n| birth_place = [[British Hong Kong]]\n| occupation = Actress, dancer, singer, tv host\n| years_active = 2007\u2013present\n| spouse = Daniel Chang (2017\u2013present)\n| awards = {{awards|award=[[TVB Anniversary Awards]]|name='''[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Popular Female Character|Most Popular Female Character]]'''<br />2016 ''[[A Fist Within Four Walls]]''}}\n| module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n| p = W\u00e1ng J\u016bnx\u012bn\n| j = Wong4 Gwan1 Hing1\n}}\n| module2 = {{infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n | background = temporary\n| origin = New York City{{Citation needed|reason=contradiction to stated Hong Kong birth place|date=November 2013}}\n| instrument = Violin, [[clarinet]] , piano\n| label = [[TVB]] Management\n}}\n}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Wang (surname)|Wong]] (\u738b)}}\n'''Grace Wong Kwan-hing'''<ref name=\"missi\">{{cite news| title=2007 Miss International| url=http://www.pageantopolis.com/international/Int_2007.htm| accessdate=9 May 2011| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718140047/http://www.pageantopolis.com/international/Int_2007.htm| archivedate=18 July 2011}}</ref> (born 5 May 1986) is a [[Hong Kong people|Hong Kong]] television actress, best known for her role as [[List of A Fist Within Four Walls characters#Fa Man|Fa Man]] in the martial arts television drama ''[[A Fist Within Four Walls]]''. She was the first runner up at the [[Miss Hong Kong 2007]] beauty pageant. She was contestant No. 9, an overseas delegate from New York City, United States. At the [[Miss International 2007]] pageant, she also made top 15 at the pageant. Grace has publicly declared that she is a devout Christian. She is close friends with [[Linda Chung]], [[Eliza Sam]], [[Leanne Li]] and [[Christine Kuo]] .<ref name=\"Popular Asians.com\">{{cite web|title=Popular Asians.com|url=http://www.popularasians.com/forum/t77005/|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413123805/http://www.popularasians.com/forum/t77005/|archivedate=13 April 2014}}</ref> Grace's acting roles for the past 10 years have shown her to be in running for one of TVB's fadan titles.\n\n== Early life ==\nWong was born in Hong Kong and emigrated to the United States with her family at the age of four. She grew up in [[Brooklyn]] and [[Queens]] in [[New York City]].<ref name=\"legend\">{{cite web|url=https://hashtaglegend.com/magazine/digital-exclusive/digital-exclusive-grace-wong/ |title=DIGITAL EXCLUSIVE: GRACE WONG |publisher=#legend |date=19 December 2018 |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> She attended [[Babson College]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.babson.edu/news/2007/11/30/rocket-pitch-to-a-crown/ |title=Rocket Pitch to a Crown |publisher=Babson Blogs |date=30 November 2007 |accessdate=27 February 2020 }}</ref> and went to Hong Kong for an exchange program at the [[Chinese University of Hong Kong]].<ref name=\"legend\"/>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 2007, Wong's career began by winning in beauty pageants. On 21 July 2007, Wong returned to Hong Kong from New York City, [[New York (state)]], U.S. and entered in the 35th Miss Hong Kong pageant as contestant No. 9. Wong was the first runner up at the [[Miss Hong Kong 2007]] beauty pageant.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television dramas===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+ \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Born Rich (TV series)|Born Rich]]''\n| Elsa Yu Yee-lam\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=3|2010\n| ''[[My Better Half (TV series)|My Better Half]]''\n| May So Sin-hung\n|\n|-\n| ''[[OL Supreme]]''\n| Margaret Chow Chi-yeuk\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Gun Metal Grey]]''\n| WPC Kong Hoi-ching (Leng Bao)\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=3|2011\n| ''[[Show Me the Happy]]''\n| Jackie\n| Episode 34\n|-\n| ''[[Relic of an Emissary]]''\n| For Yim-yim\n| \n|-\n| ''[[The Life and Times of a Sentinel]]'' \n| Ngan Yeung-suet, Consort Wai\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2012\n| ''[[House of Harmony and Vengeance]]''\n| Tai Hor-sau\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Tiger Cubs (TV series)|Tiger Cubs]]''\n| Laurine Shu Tze-lai\n| Episode 8\n|-\n| ''[[Friendly Fire (TV series)|Friendly Fire]]''\n| Moon Chuk Sheung-yuet\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| rowspan=5|2013\n| ''[[Sergeant Tabloid]]''\n| WPC Goldie Kam Sui-na\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[Awfully Lawful]]'' \n| Honey Yau Mat\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Hippocratic Crush II]]''\n| Amber Ling Kwan\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[Bounty Lady]]''\n| Yam Mo-lin\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[Return of the Silver Tongue]]''\n| Suen Chor-chor\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2014\n| ''[[Tiger Cubs II]]''\n| Laurine Shu Tze-lai\n| Episode 4\n|-\n| ''[[Come On, Cousin]]''\n| young Barbara\n| Guest star\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| ''[[Limelight Years]]''\n| Lydia Nam Ding-na\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Lord of Shanghai (TV series)|Lord of Shanghai]]''\n| Chor Ting-ting\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2016\n| ''[[Short End of the Stick (TV series)|Short End of the Stick]]''\n|  Kam Tai-tai\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Come with Me (TV series)|Come with Me]]''\n| Emma Chung Ying-man and Dan-dan\n| Role of two different characters- identical twin sisters\n|-\n| ''[[A Fist Within Four Walls]]''\n| [[List of A Fist Within Four Walls characters#Fa Man|Fa Man]]\n| [[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Popular Female Character]]<br />TVB Star Award for My Favourite TVB Drama Characters<br />[[StarHub TVB Awards|StarHub TVB Award for My Favourite TVB Female TV Characters]]<br />StarHub TVB Award for My Favourite