nt_2007.htm| accessdate=9 May 2011| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718140047/http://www.pageantopolis.com/international/Int_2007.htm| archivedate=18 July 2011}}</ref> (born 5 May 1986) is a [[Hong Kong people|Hong Kong]] television actress, best known for her role as [[List of A Fist Within Four Walls characters#Fa Man|Fa Man]] in the martial arts television drama ''[[A Fist Within Four Walls]]''. She was the first runner up at the [[Miss Hong Kong 2007]] beauty pageant. She was contestant No. 9, an overseas delegate from New York City, United States. At the [[Miss International 2007]] pageant, she also made top 15 at the pageant. Grace has publicly declared that she is a devout Christian. She is close friends with [[Linda Chung]], [[Eliza Sam]], [[Leanne Li]] and [[Christine Kuo]] .<ref name=\"Popular Asians.com\">{{cite web|title=Popular Asians.com|url=http://www.popularasians.com/forum/t77005/|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413123805/http://www.popularasians.com/forum/t77005/|archivedate=13 April 2014}}</ref> Grace's acting roles for the past 10 years have shown her to be in running for one of TVB's fadan titles.\n\n== Early life ==\nWong was born in Hong Kong and emigrated to the United States with her family at the age of four. She grew up in [[Brooklyn]] and [[Queens]] in [[New York City]].<ref name=\"legend\">{{cite web|url=https://hashtaglegend.com/magazine/digital-exclusive/digital-exclusive-grace-wong/ |title=DIGITAL EXCLUSIVE: GRACE WONG |publisher=#legend |date=19 December 2018 |accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> She attended [[Babson College]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.babson.edu/news/2007/11/30/rocket-pitch-to-a-crown/ |title=Rocket Pitch to a Crown |publisher=Babson Blogs |date=30 November 2007 |accessdate=27 February 2020 }}</ref> and went to Hong Kong for an exchange program at the [[Chinese University of Hong Kong]].<ref name=\"legend\"/>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 2007, Wong's career began by winning in beauty pageants. On 21 July 2007, Wong returned to Hong Kong from New York City, [[New York (state)]], U.S. and entered in the 35th Miss Hong Kong pageant as contestant No. 9. Wong was the first runner up at the [[Miss Hong Kong 2007]] beauty pageant.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television dramas===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+ \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Born Rich (TV series)|Born Rich]]''\n| Elsa Yu Yee-lam\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=3|2010\n| ''[[My Better Half (TV series)|My Better Half]]''\n| May So Sin-hung\n|\n|-\n| ''[[OL Supreme]]''\n| Margaret Chow Chi-yeuk\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Gun Metal Grey]]''\n| WPC Kong Hoi-ching (Leng Bao)\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=3|2011\n| ''[[Show Me the Happy]]''\n| Jackie\n| Episode 34\n|-\n| ''[[Relic of an Emissary]]''\n| For Yim-yim\n| \n|-\n| ''[[The Life and Times of a Sentinel]]'' \n| Ngan Yeung-suet, Consort Wai\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2012\n| ''[[House of Harmony and Vengeance]]''\n| Tai Hor-sau\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Tiger Cubs (TV series)|Tiger Cubs]]''\n| Laurine Shu Tze-lai\n| Episode 8\n|-\n| ''[[Friendly Fire (TV series)|Friendly Fire]]''\n| Moon Chuk Sheung-yuet\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| rowspan=5|2013\n| ''[[Sergeant Tabloid]]''\n| WPC Goldie Kam Sui-na\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[Awfully Lawful]]'' \n| Honey Yau Mat\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Hippocratic Crush II]]''\n| Amber Ling Kwan\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[Bounty Lady]]''\n| Yam Mo-lin\n| Nominated\u2014[[TVB Anniversary Award for Most Improved Female Artiste]]\n|-\n| ''[[Return of the Silver Tongue]]''\n| Suen Chor-chor\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2014\n| ''[[Tiger Cubs II]]''\n| Laurine Shu Tze-lai\n| Episod