{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/44tafm4490xYqhfQKvMD4r|title=Believe It|website=[[Spotify]]}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\"| United States\n| rowspan=\"3\"| March 31, 2020\n| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328101730/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=March 28, 2020|title=Top 40/M Future Releases}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Rhythmic contemporary]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328101822/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|archivedate=March 28, 2020|title=Top 40 Rhythmic Future Releases}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Urban contemporary]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330092129/https://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|archivedate=March 30, 2020|title=Urban/UAC Future Releases}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\"| United Kingdom\n| April 3, 2020\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408013901/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/2sgpCPqVPgjqC7tHBb97kd9/the-1xtra-playlist|date=April 8, 2020|title=BBC - The 1Xtra Playlist}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 10, 2020\n| Contemporary hit radio\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|title=BBC - Radio 1 Playlist|date=April 10, 2020|website=[[BBC Online|bbc.co.uk]]}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{PartyNextDoor}}\n{{Rihanna songs}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:PartyNextDoor songs]]\n[[Category:Rihanna songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Cardiak]]\n[[Category:Songs written by PartyNextDoor]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Rihanna]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Believe It\n| cover      = PartyNextDoor and Rihanna - Believe It.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[PartyNextDoor]] and [[Rihanna]]\n| album      = [[Partymobile]]\n| released   = {{start date|2020|03|27|mf=y}}\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"HS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/rihanna-partynextdoor-song-stream-reactions/|title=Rihanna & PARTYNEXTDOOR Just Dropped \"Believe It\" & Fans Are Going Wild|website=[[Highsnobiety]]|last=Tesema|first=Feleg|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=3}}\n| label      =\n* [[OVO Sound]]\n* [[Warner Records|Warner]]\n| writer     =\n* [[PartyNextDoor|Jahron Brathwaite]]\n* [[Robyn Fenty]]\n* Andre Robertson\n* [[Cardiak|Carl McCormick]]\n* Eric Dugar\n| producer   =\n* Bizness Boi\n* [[Cardiak]]\n* Ninetyfour\n| chronology = [[PartyNextDoor]]\n| prev_title = Split Decision\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Rihanna]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Lemon (N.E.R.D and Rihanna song)|Lemon]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = Believe It\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}} \n}}\n\"'''Believe It'''\" is a song by Canadian singer [[PartyNextDoor]] and Barbadian singer [[Rihanna]]. It was released as the fourth single from PartyNextDoor's third studio album ''[[Partymobile]]'' on March 27, 2020, and was produced by Bizness Boi, [[Cardiak]] and Ninetyfour. The song marks Rihanna's first appearance on a single in three years, following [[N.E.R.D.]]'s \"[[Lemon (N.E.R.D and Rihanna song)|Lemon]]\" (2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/rihanna-partynextdoor-new-song-believe-it-listen-1203547056/|title=Listen to PartyNextDoor's Rihanna-Featuring New Song 'Believe It'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|author=''Variety'' staff|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref> The song debuted at number 12 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and at number 23 on the [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'']] [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9352114/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-number-one-second-week-hot-100|title=The Weeknd No. 1 on Hot 100 for Second Week|date=2020-04-06|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nPartyNextDoor has previously co-written several songs with Rihanna, including \"[[Work (Rihanna song)|Work]]\", \"[[Sex with Me]]\" and \"[[Wild Thoughts]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/rihanna-and-partynextdoor-share-new-song-believe-it-listen/|title=Rihanna and PARTYNEXTDOOR Share New Song \"BELIEVE IT\": Listen|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Pierre|first=Alphonse|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Writing and recording==\nAmerican record producer [[Cardiak]] created the instrumental of the song, which features \"intertwining guitar and [a] pitched-up vocal sample\". He then sent it to Bizness Boi, who was at a writing camp in [[Paris]]; despite working on the track with an unnamed artist, he passed it on to Ninetyfour, who fleshed the song out and sent it to PartyNextDoor upon the advice of a friend. PartyNextDoor put placeholder vocals from his girlfriend on the track while waiting to hear back from Rihanna. Rihanna finished her vocals in the week of the album's release. Bizness Boi and Ninetyfour did not hear Rihanna's finished vocals on the track until the album's release on March 27.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/partynextdoor-rihanna-believe-it-making-of-972815/|title=How Rihanna Ended Up on PartyNextDoor's 'Believe It'|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Leight|first=Elias|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Lyrics and composition==\n\"Believe It\" is a \"sensual\" [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] \"slow burner\" about a relationship, with PartyNextDoor and Rihanna singing to each other as lovers \"imploring each other to believe in the power of their connection\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9344596/rihanna-partynextdoor-believe-it|title=Rihanna Jumps Back to Music With Partynextdoor on Grooving 'Believe It'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nJessica McKinney of ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' included the song among their list of Best New Music of the week, calling it a \"breezy R&B record\" and noting how Rihanna takes a backseat to Party, \"only offering raspy vocals on the chorus\", singing, \"Best make me believe it/Believe you won't deceive me. stfu\".<ref name=\"ComplexBest\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/best-new-music-this-week-partynextdoor-rihanna-future|title=Best New Music This Week: PARTYNEXTDOOR, Fivio Foreign, Murda Beatz, and More|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|28|artist=PartyNextDoor & Rihanna|song=Believe It|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|51|artist=PartyNextDoor & Rihanna|song=Believe It|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|17|artist=PartyNextDoor & Rihanna|song=Believe It|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|13|artist=PartyNextDoor & Rihanna|song=Believe It|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|56|artist=PartyNextDoor & Rihanna|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 8, 2